questions.solution:
On calcule en utilisant les valeurs usuelles :
- $f(0) = \cos 0 + 0 = 1$ ;
- $f\left(\dfrac{\pi}{2}\right) = \cos\dfrac{\pi}{2} + \dfrac{1}{2} \times \dfrac{\pi}{2} = 0 + \dfrac{\pi}{4} = \dfrac{\pi}{4}$ ;
- $f(\pi) = \cos\pi + \dfrac{\pi}{2} = -1 + \dfrac{\pi}{2} = \dfrac{\pi - 2}{2}$ ;
- $f(2\pi) = \cos(2\pi) + \pi = 1 + \pi$.
